title: Colorful Fishing Boats on Goree Island, Senegal
text:
Colorful Fishing Boats on Goree Island, Senegal 
Camera NIKON D300S Aperture f/10 Exposure Time 1/800 
Goree Island in Senegal, off the coast of Dakkar, is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and a former slave fortress which was a major focus of the 17th and 18th century slave trade. 
Today Goree is a living community with homes and businesses, including a fishing trade. These are some of the boats which the local fishermen use to go get their catch.
